<br>
If the technology works as it should, this GUARANTEES that there will always be entertaining content for groups to engage that will be challenging and rewarding.<br>
<br>
No worries about some gimp that plays EQ for a LIVING monopolizing the spawn at lewtcamp_069.<br>
<br>
No worries of kill stealing, ninja looting, or trains!<br>
<br>
If the quality of the content is high enough, and diverse enough, this easilly has the potential to be the best expansion to date.  <br>
<br>
If they balance the encounters appropriately to the power level of the groups entering the dungeons and reward appropriately to meet the risk VS reward it will be the first sign from Sony in a long time that alternatives are available other than joining Uberguild_X to experience &quot;end game&quot; level challenges in EQ.<br>
<br>
I actually hope that there are many &quot;key phrases&quot; which can be said to the dungeon quest NPCs, which will in essense indicate &quot;Yes, I want a VERY difficult dungeon encounter&quot; or &quot;I'll take the usual, thanks!&quot;... not to dumb down the dungeons so much, but to provide a means by which players can indicate they want a REAL challenge.  There is a big difference between the power of an Elemental Planes equipped group with maxed out AA abilities, and a group of newly level 65 characters that are barely discovering PoS/PoV... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13322<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 7:51 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lost Dungeons of Norrath Interview</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> I wonder about the impact on community. Sure its nice to know you can get a camp, but there was always something interesting and organic around how camps developed in certain dungeons and how communities, protocols and friendships developed around these.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It might have been interesting in the end, but it was always stupid to have the deadly lair of some evil entity to be staked out like the mall in December.<br>
